    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You need to use the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/math/BigDecimal.html#doubleValue()\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>doubleValue()</code></a> method to get the double value from a BigDecimal object.</p>\n<pre><code>BigDecimal bd; // the value you get/receive from your source\n\n// In case there is a chance that the incoming BigDecimal value is  null,\n// please add an appropriate null check before you invoke the doubleValue() method on that object.\ndouble d = bd.doubleValue(); // The &quot;double&quot; you want\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2678195,
      "reputation" : 68865,
      "user_id" : 2314073,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 56,
